# =============================================================================
# config/npm-globals.list — npm global packages to install and keep updated
#
# These are installed via: npm install -g <package>
# Uses the Homebrew-managed Node.js npm (not the system apt npm).
#
# Format: <package-name>[@version]  [# description]
# Specify @latest to always install the latest version.
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Examples:
#   typescript          # TypeScript compiler
#   yarn                # Yarn package manager
#   pnpm                # pnpm package manager
#   @anthropic-ai/sdk   # Anthropic SDK (for testing)
# =============================================================================

# Currently no additional global npm packages beyond npm itself.
# npm itself is managed by Homebrew via the `node` formula.
# Add packages here as needed.
